						<div class="postbody"><div class="quotetitle">getafixx wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">Perhaps making a mapper based on MMC3 that offered a 8Mbit PRG and CHR would be a good thing to design</div><br />The design is rather trivial and already done supported by some emulators I believe?  Just use bits 6 &amp; 7 of the PRG bank registers and you've got support for 2MByte of PRG-ROM.  I think there's some megaman hack with MMC3 that's 1MByte someone was asking me to support years ago but I've kinda forgotten about it since.  In general the non-standard options I offer to homebrew developers in private discussions is turned down due to lack of emulator support despite the fact it wouldn't increase board cost.<br /><br />EDIT: I neglected expanding CHR beyond 256KByte.  I agree it would be nice to have a standard definition of how to do this, but it's a bit difficult esp without software.  Perhaps some unused $A000/A001 bits could be used, but probably best to define 8 more registers in bank select register $8000 with unused bit 3.</div>

					
